This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with named-entity recognition, which is a subfield of natural language processing. Additionally, the use of neural networks for learning and the comparison of different models also suggest a focus on machine learning and computational linguistics. 

The paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the development and comparison of different machine learning models. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as named-entity recognition is a common task in AI and the use of neural networks is a popular approach in this field. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possibility as the paper focuses on the use of neural networks for named-entity recognition. 

Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a potential sub-category as named-entity recognition is often used in information retrieval tasks, and the paper may involve the use of tag hierarchies to improve retrieval performance.
